															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/djoric" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(388108); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=388108&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610227603" alt="Djoric" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=388108)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/djoric" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(388108); return false;" >Djoric</a></span> <span class="odate time_1340121693 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">19 Jun 2012 16:01</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1484163">
									

<p>I always see the Chaos Insurgency as &quot;those guys&quot;, when it comes to the GOI. They're handy if you need someone to do a raid on a Foundation site, but beyond that there's not a whole lot to them.</p>
<p>Anyway, when I read &quot;Chaos Insurgency&quot;, even if that's a title the Foundation gave them, I don't see any sort of evul Foundation. I see a chaotic, disorganized, terrorist group interested in shedding as much blood as possible, as crudely and as violently as possible. Quite honestly, the organized, deadly, sneakity-sneak Insurgency in the GOI list could use a better name. Maybe this CI works for them, who knows.</p>
<p>So basically chaos cultists from Warhmmer, without the cult. &quot;BLOOD JUST BECAUSE!&quot;</p>

							</div>

								
